  "title": "Logistics and Operations Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>1. Plan, oversee, and optimize daily logistics and warehouse operations.</p><p>2. Develop and implement strategies to improve operational efficiency and cost-effectiveness.</p><p>3. Manage and mentor a team of warehouse staff, including training and performance reviews.</p><p>4. Coordinate with suppliers, vendors, and clients to ensure timely delivery of goods.</p><p>5. Utilize data analytics tools to monitor and report on key performance metrics.</p><p>6. Ensure compliance with safety regulations and company policies in warehouse operations.</p><p>7. Collaborate with cross-functional teams to streamline supply chain processes.</p><p>8.Collaborating with sales and customer service teams to ensure timely and accurate order fulfillment and delivery, maintaining high levels of customer satisfaction.</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><p>1. Bachelor’s degree in Logistics, Supply Chain Management, Business, or a related field.</p><p>2. At least 3-5 years of experience in logistics, supply chain, or operations management.</p><p>3. Strong leadership and organizational skills.</p><p>4. Proficiency in logistics software (e.g., WMS, TMS) and data analytics tools.</p><p>5. Excellent problem-solving abilities and attention to detail.</p><p>6. Knowledge of Singapore’s logistics and warehousing regulations is an advantage.</p><p>7.Excellent planning and organizational skills .</p><p>8.Team leadership and management skills .</p><p><u><strong>Need to work PH and weekend and night shift based on bussiness demand.</strong></u></p><p>We thank you for your interest and we regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. All resumes received will be used for recruitment purposes only.</p><p>EA License ID: 18C9520</p><p>EA Registration ID: R1765753</p>",
